{"name":"Mine, Breach Charge","type":"weapon","img":"icons/weapons/thrown/bomb-timer.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>This is a breaching charge that may be attached to a door or a wall. This deals 3d6 concussive damage to creatures and objects within 5 feet of it, with a DC 12 saving throw to half damage. Against objects, it deals double damage, but half damage against creatures. This usually is applied with a delaying fuse (1d4 rounds), but the fuse can be changed normally.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[warcraft5e.wc5e_mechanics.AVFXnaErI2AsW30o]{Focused} @Compendium[warcraft5e.wc5e_mechanics.0kkX8fLDVucLKRE4]{Reliable Device}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Mine</strong></p>\n<p>Mines are explosive traps that explode when stepped on (unless modified with a fuse). A mine can be detected with a successful Spirit (Perception) check and disarmed with a successful Agility (Thieves‘ Tools) check against the Device save DC, and is treated as a trap. The mine must pass a successful malfunction roll test.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Wc5e - Core p. 222","quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":20,"attunement":0,"equipped":false,"rarity":"common","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":5,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"sphere"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":"self"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":""},"consume":{"type":"ammo","target":"","amount":1},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":"0","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[["3d6","concussive"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":12,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialR","baseItem":"generalExplosive","properties":{"ada":false,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"hvyplus":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"mgc":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"si